cs.HC, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.CY, cs.IR 

This paper discusses the design of a user interface for Amazon Mechanical Turk workers to improve the quality of image annotation for marine life monitoring. The paper focuses on the human factors involved in designing Human Intelligence Tasks (HITs) and uses the Self-Determination Theory to enhance worker motivation and competence. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). The paper also involves the use of machine learning algorithms for image analysis, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of annotated images for fish stock estimation, which is related to cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.CY (Computers and Society). Finally, the paper involves the use of crowdsourcing for image annotation, which falls under cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
